Repost @tfbrewing with @get.repost
・・・
HEY SLC!! A little taste of California releases tomorrow! 

Stay tuned for tasting notes, limits and pricing!

Remember when Kyle from @horusagedales came to visit? We all thought we would be brewing a barrel-aged doozy, which we did-but that won’t be ready until next year…

Kyle flew in from San Diego and insisted that we brew a Pilsner! 

Now your speaking our language!! 

He introduced us to the crew @admiralmaltings. Using their Limited Edition Atlas Pilsner-Style malt, together we brewed Atlas Zwickelbier!! 

From Admirial Maltings:
“This malt is a throwback to a forgotten era of Northern California malting and brewing. 

The Spanish first brought Atlas to California (it's named for Atlas Mountains in Morocco). Atlas was grown throughout the Sacramento Valley and even exported to England from the 1860s until WWII. All of Admiral's malts are produced from grain grown sustainably by California family farms. The Atlas barley used for this malt was grown on the Work Ranch in San Miguel, CA.” 
#tfbrewing #horusagedales #admiralmaltings #saltlakecity #oceansidecalifornia #alamedacalifornia #atlaspils #zwickelbier #prost
